 of its public query DSL is macro/inline-oriented, so a plain Java scaffold may need to focus on callable JDBC context APIs or otherwise account for Scala-facing APIs.\\\",\\n    \\\"If generated tests choose PostgreSQL, MySQL, SQLite, SQL Server, or Oracle contexts instead of H2, they would need different drivers and possibly Docker; H2 is the lowest-friction documented path.\\\"\\n  ]\\n}\",\"textSignature\":\"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_0c90ea7d82497795016a3c5a605f3881908cb1d32bbd17667f\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}],\"api\":\"openai-responses\",\"provider\":\"OCA\",\"model\":\"oca/gpt-5.5\",\"usage\":{\"input\":32300,\"output\":866,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":33166,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0}},\"stopReason\":\"stop\",\"timestamp\":1782340179684,\"responseId\":\"resp_0c90ea7d82497795016a3c5a54ff58819082267ac8472d8607\"}}\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
