ual JDBC driver/database, and the resolved artifact does not bring one transitively for consumers.\\\\\\\",\\\\n  \\\\\\\"deterministic_setup\\\\\\\": [\\\\n    {\\\\n      \\\\\\\"kind\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"dependency\\\\\\\",\\\\n      \\\\\\\"coordinate\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"com.h2database:h2:2.3.230\\\\\\\",\\\\n      \\\\\\\"scope\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"testImplementation\\\\\\\",\\\\n      \\\\\\\"reason\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"The upstream quill-jdbc documentation lists a separate JDBC driver dependency for each database, including H2, and the artifact POM only uses H2 as an upstream test dependency. An in-memory H2 database is enough to exercise H2JdbcContext without Docker.\\\\\\\"\\\\n    }\\\\n  ],\\\\n  \\\\\\\"agent_guidance\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Use an in-memory JDBC DataSource in the test setup, preferably org.h2.jdbcx.JdbcDataSource with a unique jdbc:h2:mem:... URL such as DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1;DB_CLOSE_ON_EXIT=FALSE, then pass it to the H2JdbcContext DataSource constructor and create/drop the test table explicitly before running Quill operations. No external service or system property should be required.\\\\\\\",\\\\n  \\\\\\\"risks\\\\\\\": [\\\\n    \\\\\\\"Quill/ProtoQuill is Scala 3 and much of its public query DSL is macro/inline-oriented, so a plain Java scaffold may need to focus on callable JDBC context APIs or otherwise account for Scala-facing APIs.\\\\\\\",\\\\n    \\\\\\\"If generated tests choose PostgreSQL, MySQL, SQLite, SQL Server, or Oracle contexts instead of H2, they would need different drivers and possibly Docker; H2 is the lowest-friction documented path.\\\\\\\"\\\\n  ]\\\\n}\\\",\\\"textSignature\\\":\\\"{\\\\\\\"v\\\\\\\":1,\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"msg_0c90ea7d82497795016a3c5a605f3881908cb1d32bbd17667f\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"phase\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"final_answer\\\\\\\"}\\\"}],\\\"api\\\":\\\"openai-responses\\\",\\\"provider\\\":\\\"OCA\\\",\\\"model\\\":\\\"oca/gpt-5.5\\\",\\\"usage\\\":{\\\"input\\\":32300,\\\"output\\\":866,\\\"cacheRead\\\":0,\\\"cacheWrite\\\":0,\\\"totalTokens\\\":33166,\\\"cost\\\":{\\\"input\\\":0,\\\"output\\\":0,\\\"cacheRead\\\":0,\\\"cacheWrite\\\":0,\\\"total\\\":0}},\\\"stopReason\\\":\\\"stop\\\",\\\"timestamp\\\":1782340179684,\\\"responseId\\\":\\\"resp_0c90ea7d82497795016a3c5a54ff58819082267ac8472d8607\\\"}}\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_28\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"The saved session is informative: the only artifact for this issue is the `library-preparation-preflight` log, and it records an `advisory_preparation` outcome rather than any generated test or Gradle execution. I’m checking whether the worktree contains partial `quill-jdbc_3:4.8.6` files or a scratch metrics repo; if not, that absence is part of the evidence.\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_29\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/zsh -lc 'git branch --show-current'\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_29\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/zsh -lc 'git branch --show-current'\",\"aggregated_output\":\"ai/kimeta/human-intervention/issue-4875-library-new-request-io.getquill-quill-jdbc_3-4.8.6-957fb010\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_30\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/zsh -lc \\\"find /home/mihailo/git -maxdepth 6 -type d | rg 'scratch.*4875|4875.*scratch|metrics.*4875|4875.*metrics|quill-jdbc_3.*4\\\\\\\\.8\\\\\\\\.6'\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_31\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/zsh -lc 'git status --short'\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_32\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"c